dct_description_sm: This polygon shapefile represents Lafitte Greenway Project for New Orleans, LA in 2017. The Lafitte Greenway, a major part of the Lafitte Greenway Corridor, is a 3.1-mile long strip of land bounded by Basin Street, Lafitte Avenue, N. Jefferson Davis Parkway, and St. Louis Street and including the entire St. Louis Street right-of-way between N. Jefferson Davis Parkway and Canal Boulevard. http://lafittecorridorconnection.com/This file was downloaded on December, 2018 by NYU Data Services. It was originally represented on the New Orleans Open Data Socrata portal as catalog record qdze-iuzu
